## Reading Markdown Files

Use AGENTMAP.md first for file search/discovery.
Flow: read AGENTMAP.md -> identify file -> read AGENT:NAV -> jump to section.

AGENT:NAV appears immediately after frontmatter so you can 
read a files first 50 lines then use AGENT:NAV to target reads.

- If purpose does not match your task stop reading.
- Use s;n ranges: Read(offset=s; limit=n).
- `>` is a hint delimiter: text after `>` lists subsections not directly in the nav. Do not use `>` in about/purpose prose.
- **Use the nav block instead of grep.** When you need a specific section; read the nav block's s;n offsets directly — no search required. Grep costs a tool-call round-trip; the nav block costs zero.

## After Editing or Creating Markdown Files

0. Once per session: run `agentmap guide` for nav writing instructions (skip if already in context)
1. Run: `agentmap update <changed files>` — refreshes line numbers; adds nav blocks to new files; flags auto-generated descriptions
2. For entries with "(auto-generated; needs review)" — rewrite the description in the nav block to remove the `~` prefix
3. Run: `agentmap update <files>` again — syncs AGENTMAP.md index with your descriptions
4. Run: `agentmap check <files>` — validates nav blocks are in sync before committing
5. Commit
